keys,en
dialogue.caretaker_intro.0,"You came back. I'd hoped — well. A year is a long time to hope for something."
dialogue.caretaker_intro.1,"What happened to it? The core — it's gone."
dialogue.caretaker_intro.2,"Gone. One night the cracks just... gave way. We don't know who. We may never know."
dialogue.caretaker_intro.3,"But you're here now. And that matters more than the why. There are people you should speak to — they'll want to see you're still alive."
dialogue.blacksmith_intro.0,"You've got some nerve, showing up now."
dialogue.blacksmith_intro.1,"...I came as soon as I heard."
dialogue.blacksmith_intro.2,"Sure you did. Fine. You're here, that's what counts. I'm not much for talking. If you want to help, get to work."
dialogue.witch_intro.0,"Ah. You. I wondered when the town would pull you back."
dialogue.witch_intro.1,"You knew I was coming?"
dialogue.witch_intro.2,"I know things are wrong. I've known since the night it happened — something in the residue of it. It didn't feel like an accident. But I can't say more than that. Not yet."
dialogue.caretaker_intro_return.0,"Good. They're still standing. That's more than I feared, some nights."
dialogue.caretaker_intro_return.1,"The Witch thinks it wasn't an accident."
dialogue.caretaker_intro_return.2,"She's not wrong to feel that way. The Undoing doesn't shatter cores — it corrupts them, slowly. Something else finished it. But we can't rebuild on grief. We rebuild on work. Start with the Town Hall — it was the heart of this place. Let's make it a heart again."
dialogue.caretaker_intro_return.3,"You'll need this. The forest won't give up its wood without a fight."
dialogue.caretaker_requirements.0,"The Town Hall first. It's where decisions were made, where people gathered when things went wrong. If we raise it, people will believe the rest is possible."
dialogue.caretaker_requirements.1,"How much wood are we talking?"
dialogue.caretaker_requirements.2,"Ten good pieces. The old pines at the forest edge — they're still standing. They always outlast everything else."
dialogue.caretaker_in_progress.0,"The forest is just east of the ruins. The trees there are old — they won't mind giving a little for this."
dialogue.caretaker_rebuild_town_hall.0,"There. It's not what it was, but it's standing. Do you know how long I stood here looking at the rubble, wondering if anyone would come?"
dialogue.caretaker_rebuild_town_hall.1,"You could have started without me."
dialogue.caretaker_rebuild_town_hall.2,"No. Some things need to be done together, or they don't mean anything. The Blacksmith is next. He won't ask for help — you'll have to offer it. And you'll need more than an axe for what he needs."
dialogue.caretaker_rebuild_town_hall.3,"Stone and coal now. The forest gave us a hall. The mountain will give us fire."
dialogue.blacksmith_requirements.0,"You want to fix the forge. Fine. I won't pretend I don't need the help."
dialogue.blacksmith_requirements.1,"What do you need?"
dialogue.blacksmith_requirements.2,"Wood for the frame. Coal for the fuel. Iron for the anvil and the fittings. None of it's easy to find since the collapse, but it's out there. Don't bring me bad iron. I'll know."
dialogue.blacksmith_requirements.3,"Coal's deeper in the mine, past the first dark. Bring a light if you have one."
dialogue.blacksmith_deliver_wood.0,"Good timber. Dry enough. Keep going."
dialogue.blacksmith_deliver_coal.0,"This'll do. You didn't complain once, did you. Huh."
dialogue.blacksmith_deliver_iron.0,"That's the last of it. You know, I thought about leaving after it happened. Didn't see the point of a forge with no town. Glad I didn't."
dialogue.blacksmith_complete.0,"The forge is lit. First time since... well."
dialogue.blacksmith_complete.1,"How does it feel?"
dialogue.blacksmith_complete.2,"Like something. Go see the Witch. She's been waiting longer than any of us."
dialogue.witch_requirements.0,"I've been piecing it back together in my head for months. The ingredients I lost, the shelves, the light from that particular window. You can't replace everything. But you can make it liveable again."
dialogue.witch_requirements.1,"Tell me what you need."
dialogue.witch_requirements.2,"Herbs from the east meadow — the ones that survived the collapse, near the old stone wall. Crystal shards from the ruins near the core. And wood, of course. Always wood. The shards are important. I want to study them. Something about the way the core broke doesn't sit right with me."
dialogue.witch_requirements.3,"Be careful with the shards. They still carry a charge. Don't pocket them near anything you're fond of."
dialogue.witch_deliver_herbs.0,"Yes. These are the right ones. I can already smell what I'll make first. Smell is the most honest sense — it doesn't lie to you the way eyes do."
dialogue.witch_deliver_crystal.0,"There's a direction to the fracture. Whoever — or whatever — caused this was standing somewhere specific. I just don't know where yet."
dialogue.witch_deliver_wood.0,"That's everything. It already feels less like a wound."
dialogue.witch_complete.0,"It's not finished. It won't be finished for a long time. But it's mine again."
dialogue.witch_complete.1,"What did the crystal shards tell you?"
dialogue.witch_complete.2,"That the core didn't fail. It was ended. Someone stood in the keeper's circle and made a choice. That takes knowledge most people in this town don't have. Most people."
dialogue.caretaker_fallback.0,"Every stone we lay is a promise. I have to believe that."
dialogue.blacksmith_fallback.0,"Work to do. Always more work to do."
dialogue.witch_fallback.0,"The town is quieter than it should be. I'm still listening."
